Now, plug in the values:

Number of H+ ions = 0.01 M x 1000 mL x 6.022 x 10^23 particles/mole

Number of H+ ions ≈ 6.022 x 10^22 ions

So, there are approximately 6.022 x 10^22 H+ ions in 1.0 L of the solution when the pH is 2.0.assistant

I hope that helps!
